The paper discusses the classification problem in the context of information theory and proposes a new approach to neural network training. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions experiments conducted to compare the performance of the proposed approach with traditional methods, which suggests it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the use of information theory in the proposed approach makes it possible for the paper to belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
